Nipah virus - Malaysia (15) 990518194240
[1
Date: Tue, 1 Jun 1999
From: Chan Yow Cheong mailto:chanyowcheong@pacific.net.sg
ProMED-mail Regional Moderator for Asia
Source: Bernama ex The Straits Times, 1 Jun 1999 [edited

Two workers at a pig farm in Sungai Buloh in Selangor died of the Nipah
virus, taking the total death toll to 103 since the outbreak began in
October [1998.
A spokesman for the Selangor JE operations room said one worker died last
Friday and the other last Saturday at the Kuala Lumpur Hospital. They had
been hospitalised since May 15, the spokesman said. The spokesman said the
authorities had placed three pig farms in Sungai Buloh under quarantine
since the two cases were detected.
******
[2
Date: Tue, 01 Jun 1999 06:40:29 -0400
From: Marjorie P. Pollack <pollackmp@mindspring.com>
Source: Asia Pulse, 05/31/1999 22:57

Another victim of Nipah virus - a 68-year old woman from Sungei Buloh died
in University Hospital. Earlier two pig farm workers who were suspected to
have been infected with the virus from Sungei Buloh died in Kuala Lumpur
Hospital last week.
